{"data":{"pages":{"edges":[{"node":{"html":"<h1>black pepper beef soup attempt #1</h1>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/c8c13260da6428bf1b86591e5aefbbbb/d3c45/pepper-soup-attempt-one.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 102.7027027027027%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"soup in a dutch oven covered by a healthy layer of peppercorns\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/c8c13260da6428bf1b86591e5aefbbbb/1c72d/pepper-soup-attempt-one.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/c8c13260da6428bf1b86591e5aefbbbb/a80bd/pepper-soup-attempt-one.jpg 148w,\n/static/c8c13260da6428bf1b86591e5aefbbbb/1c91a/pepper-soup-attempt-one.jpg 295w,\n/static/c8c13260da6428bf1b86591e5aefbbbb/1c72d/pepper-soup-attempt-one.jpg 590w,\n/static/c8c13260da6428bf1b86591e5aefbbbb/a8a14/pepper-soup-attempt-one.jpg 885w,\n/static/c8c13260da6428bf1b86591e5aefbbbb/fbd2c/pepper-soup-attempt-one.jpg 1180w,\n/static/c8c13260da6428bf1b86591e5aefbbbb/d3c45/pepper-soup-attempt-one.jpg 3472w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\nadapted Andy Cook's yukgaejang but skipped the gochugaru/garlic/sesame oil and fernbrake, and added 1/4-1/2 cup black peppercorns.</p>\n<p>i tasted it and I think it needs an additional ingredient and accent flavor to round it out. Also add herbs next time.  filter the peppercorns after the broth is done.</p>\n<p>some suggested pairings i found for next time:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>garlic</li>\n<li>basil</li>\n<li>ginger</li>\n<li>parsley</li>\n<li>thyme</li>\n<li>peas</li>\n<li>scallions</li>\n<li>spinach</li>\n<li>vegetables</li>\n<li>radishes maybe too as garnish</li>\n</ul>","parent":{"name":"black pepper soup attempt one"}}},{"node":{"html":"<h1>Culinary Experiments</h1>\n<p>A log of recipes that I have tried.</p>\n<h2>Black Pepper Beef Soup</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n2026-03-17: <a href=\"/black pepper soup attempt one\" title=\"black pepper soup attempt one\">black pepper soup attempt one</a>\n</li>\n</ul>","parent":{"name":"culinary experiments"}}},{"node":{"html":"<h1>coasters</h1>\n<p>i used some leftover wood and veneer for these because i wanted to get some practice doing that. they came out ok. i was not very careful to sand precisely to final dimensions so they are not super accurate.</p>\n<p>however, the friend who received them reports that they do in fact work so that's a win!</p>\n<p>todo: pictures</p>","parent":{"name":"coasters"}}},{"node":{"html":"<h1>dyrlund restoration</h1>\n<p>i bought a fancy table*! the tradeoff was that the top had been (poorly) veneered at some point, so i wanted to find a solution for that.</p>\n<p>the sellers (who were very nice and delivered to my house / showed me how to assemble) suggested i just flip the top and use the bottom side as the new table top.</p>\n<p>i thought about stripping the aftermarket veneer off but getting a good quality veneering on a surface this big is something i don't want to try for the first time on such a nice piece of furniture. so i did as they suggested.</p>\n<p>this meant i just needed to flip the table top and then drill holes through so that i could screw the brackets in on the reverse side. i ended up using my pin vice because i was impatient and it worked.</p>\n<p>after that there were the existing screw holes and one central hole on the (formerly) bottom side of the table top so i wanted to  fill them. i tried some leftover mother-of-pearl i had lying around but that looked bad so instead i got some dowels off of amazon and carved them down until they fit snug. then i carved them (carefully) flush with the table top and i was done!</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/3cfc92fa504030b5ff0a93d757d49f71/d3c45/dyrlund-dowel-and-mop-compare.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 133.1081081081081%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"dowel held next to a hole it will eventually be jammed into\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/3cfc92fa504030b5ff0a93d757d49f71/1c72d/dyrlund-dowel-and-mop-compare.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/3cfc92fa504030b5ff0a93d757d49f71/a80bd/dyrlund-dowel-and-mop-compare.jpg 148w,\n/static/3cfc92fa504030b5ff0a93d757d49f71/1c91a/dyrlund-dowel-and-mop-compare.jpg 295w,\n/static/3cfc92fa504030b5ff0a93d757d49f71/1c72d/dyrlund-dowel-and-mop-compare.jpg 590w,\n/static/3cfc92fa504030b5ff0a93d757d49f71/a8a14/dyrlund-dowel-and-mop-compare.jpg 885w,\n/static/3cfc92fa504030b5ff0a93d757d49f71/fbd2c/dyrlund-dowel-and-mop-compare.jpg 1180w,\n/static/3cfc92fa504030b5ff0a93d757d49f71/d3c45/dyrlund-dowel-and-mop-compare.jpg 3472w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/7705cce3b94c0099cf7068427097797e/afef0/dyrlund-tools-shot.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"wood shavings and knife and a toolbox\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/7705cce3b94c0099cf7068427097797e/1c72d/dyrlund-tools-shot.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/7705cce3b94c0099cf7068427097797e/a80bd/dyrlund-tools-shot.jpg 148w,\n/static/7705cce3b94c0099cf7068427097797e/1c91a/dyrlund-tools-shot.jpg 295w,\n/static/7705cce3b94c0099cf7068427097797e/1c72d/dyrlund-tools-shot.jpg 590w,\n/static/7705cce3b94c0099cf7068427097797e/a8a14/dyrlund-tools-shot.jpg 885w,\n/static/7705cce3b94c0099cf7068427097797e/fbd2c/dyrlund-tools-shot.jpg 1180w,\n/static/7705cce3b94c0099cf7068427097797e/afef0/dyrlund-tools-shot.jpg 4624w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>(did I say carefully? i put several scrapes in my thumbs. safety <em>should</em> be first if you try this at home)</p>\n<p>*it is called a dyrlund lotus table i think. most of the ones online are much more expensive than mine was</p>","parent":{"name":"dyrlund restoration"}}},{"node":{"html":"<h1>gochujang salad dressing</h1>\na result of one of my <a href=\"/culinary experiments\" title=\"culinary experiments\">culinary experiments</a> but this one came together just fine on the first try so i am not going to bother to list it that way.\n<h2>ingredients</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>~1 part rice vinegar</li>\n<li>~1 part sesame oil</li>\n<li>gochugaru to taste</li>\n<li>gochujang to taste</li>\n<li>spoonful of soy sauce (maybe ~1/4 part or something)</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>instructions</h2>\n<p>combine all ingredients. throw on leafy greens like spinach, scallions, etc.</p>","parent":{"name":"gochujang salad dressing"}}},{"node":{"html":"<h1>headboard</h1>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/bbf6537a4abf3717fa7b3b0073118fa2/e83a7/headboard.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 72.2972972972973%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"faux linen headboard\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/bbf6537a4abf3717fa7b3b0073118fa2/1c72d/headboard.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/bbf6537a4abf3717fa7b3b0073118fa2/a80bd/headboard.jpg 148w,\n/static/bbf6537a4abf3717fa7b3b0073118fa2/1c91a/headboard.jpg 295w,\n/static/bbf6537a4abf3717fa7b3b0073118fa2/1c72d/headboard.jpg 590w,\n/static/bbf6537a4abf3717fa7b3b0073118fa2/a8a14/headboard.jpg 885w,\n/static/bbf6537a4abf3717fa7b3b0073118fa2/fbd2c/headboard.jpg 1180w,\n/static/bbf6537a4abf3717fa7b3b0073118fa2/e83a7/headboard.jpg 3158w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>i wanted to get one of those mortise-and-tenon joint bedframes but the cheap one did not come with a headboard. so i made my own!</p>\n<p>i used an ikea desk (don't remember what it is called but about as wide as the frame), and bought upholstery batting, a mattress topper, and a linen-look shower curtain.</p>\n<p>i stapled the mattress topper to the desk top (i also bought a staple gun for this!) and then stapled the batting over it, and then finally the shower curtain.</p>\n<p>this ended up ok, but the shower curtain is not a great texture or match for my sheets (it's about the same color) so i want to change it. i will probably buy real upholstery fabric this time because i can do with just 2 yards i think maybe three.</p>","parent":{"name":"headboard"}}},{"node":{"html":"<h1>hummus</h1>\n<p>surely this recipe is not original but it is at least nice for myself to remember</p>\n<h2>ingredients</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>1 can chickpeas\n<ul>\n<li>you can wash and shell them if you are feeling <strong>extra</strong> but it is optional and a lot of work</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>tahini</li>\n<li>olive oil</li>\n<li>lemon juice</li>\n<li>1-2 cloves garlic</li>\n<li>salt (carthage)</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>instructions</h2>\n<p>rinse and maybe shell the chickpeas (up to thou, who knoweth thine level of commitment greater than this humble author).</p>\n<p>put ingredients into food processor and process them as this is its sacred purpose.</p>\n<p>adjust quantities of other stuff based on taste.</p>","parent":{"name":"hummus"}}},{"node":{"html":"<h1>memento mori</h1>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/e94204cd9c2c18cfae1937ae4a1cd06c/d3c45/watch-art.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 133.1081081081081%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"a frame with walnut burl veneer in the background and watch pieces arranged in the shape of a tree\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/e94204cd9c2c18cfae1937ae4a1cd06c/1c72d/watch-art.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/e94204cd9c2c18cfae1937ae4a1cd06c/a80bd/watch-art.jpg 148w,\n/static/e94204cd9c2c18cfae1937ae4a1cd06c/1c91a/watch-art.jpg 295w,\n/static/e94204cd9c2c18cfae1937ae4a1cd06c/1c72d/watch-art.jpg 590w,\n/static/e94204cd9c2c18cfae1937ae4a1cd06c/a8a14/watch-art.jpg 885w,\n/static/e94204cd9c2c18cfae1937ae4a1cd06c/fbd2c/watch-art.jpg 1180w,\n/static/e94204cd9c2c18cfae1937ae4a1cd06c/d3c45/watch-art.jpg 3472w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>a commission for a coworker. i made one of these spontaneously because turns out you can just buy watch parts from ebay! and then they saw it and wanted one</p>\n<p>i think this one came out much better and i credit that to the financial incentive and i guess the fact that i had in fact done one before</p>","parent":{"name":"memento mori"}}},{"node":{"html":"<h1>pajama shirt</h1>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/817ac881aeeec67bd7f34b90261c6d0d/d3c45/hippari-closeup.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 133.1081081081081%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"close-up of blue linen fabric with a fancy leaf shaped stitch in yellow thread\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/817ac881aeeec67bd7f34b90261c6d0d/1c72d/hippari-closeup.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/817ac881aeeec67bd7f34b90261c6d0d/a80bd/hippari-closeup.jpg 148w,\n/static/817ac881aeeec67bd7f34b90261c6d0d/1c91a/hippari-closeup.jpg 295w,\n/static/817ac881aeeec67bd7f34b90261c6d0d/1c72d/hippari-closeup.jpg 590w,\n/static/817ac881aeeec67bd7f34b90261c6d0d/a8a14/hippari-closeup.jpg 885w,\n/static/817ac881aeeec67bd7f34b90261c6d0d/fbd2c/hippari-closeup.jpg 1180w,\n/static/817ac881aeeec67bd7f34b90261c6d0d/d3c45/hippari-closeup.jpg 3472w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>i made a set of pajamas over thanksgiving 2025 at my parents' but i improvised the shirt and it was kinda bad.</p>\n<p>so i bought a <a href=\"https://www.folkwear.com/products/japanese-field-clothing\">hippari pattern</a> because that looked like it would be an interesting shirt to use as pajamas.</p>\n<p>i got blue linen and also i had bought a sewing machine for my new apartment because why would i want to <em>not</em> have a tool lying around?</p>\n<p>i made a muslin that came out decent so i just did the real one as soon as the blue arrived. after i was done i figured the fancy leaf stitch would look good around the edges with yellow thread so i did that on a slower speed.</p>\n<p>todo: picture of it being worn if i am brave enough for that</p>","parent":{"name":"pajama shirt"}}},{"node":{"html":"<h1>projects</h1>\n<p>anything i finish that is reasonably interesting enough to share</p>\n<p>some things i cannot post yet as they are ungiven gifts</p>\n<h2>arts</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"/memento mori\" title=\"memento mori\">memento mori</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>crafts and diy</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"/coasters\" title=\"coasters\">coasters</a>\n</li>\n<li>\n<a href=\"/dyrlund restoration\" title=\"dyrlund restoration\">dyrlund restoration</a>\n</li>\n<li>\n<a href=\"/headboard\" title=\"headboard\">headboard</a>\n</li>\n<li>\n<a href=\"/pajama shirt\" title=\"pajama shirt\">pajama shirt</a>\n</li>\n</ul>","parent":{"name":"projects"}}},{"node":{"html":"<h1>recipes</h1>\n<p>finished recipes are published here! results may (and should) vary</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"/gochujang salad dressing\" title=\"gochujang salad dressing\">gochujang salad dressing</a>\n</li>\n<li>\n<a href=\"/hummus\" title=\"hummus\">hummus</a>\n</li>\n</ul>","parent":{"name":"recipes"}}},{"node":{"html":"<p>just some guy, really</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"/recipes\" title=\"recipes\">recipes</a>, and by extension:\n<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"/culinary experiments\" title=\"culinary experiments\">culinary experiments</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<a href=\"/projects\" title=\"projects\">projects</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>todos:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>adjust the theming!!</li>\n<li>take more pictures and stuff</li>\n</ul>","parent":{"name":"index"}}}]}}}